563. ·And also that definite periods are fixed sor creatures ac- cording to their kind....'

For example, all horses come to maturity in three years. The reason is that the atoms‚ which form the starting-point for the making of a new horse, remain for ever identical. If the atoms could grow smaller, each new generation of horses would take longer to come to maturity.
